        "text": "Formula Bar",
        "bbox": [
          0.26591760491546207,
          0.08134920599958431,
          0.4063670410349124,
          0.09747023774561606
        ],
        "order": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_docstructbench_llm-raw-the-eye-o.O-1%20Excel.pdf_12_2",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The tormula bar appears below the Ribbon (Figure 1-12a). As you type, Excel displays the entry in the formula bar. You can make the formula bar larger by dragging the sizing handle (Figure 1-7) on the formula bar or clicking the expand button to the right of the formula bar. Excel also displays the active cell reference in the Name box on the left side of the formula bar.",
        "bbox": [
          0.2640449466172411,
          0.10755813950399183,
          0.9176029870806487,
          0.18030753955385848
        ],
        "order": 3
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0002",
    "kind": "section_text_panel",
